title: Kids health outcomes have more to do with parents level of education than income

title_detail.value: Kids health outcomes have more to do with parents level of education than income

summary: A recent study finds that parents educated beyond high school have healthier families, as they invest more in family health care which reduces the likelihood of adverse medical conditions.
